## SQL Analysis

Google BigQuery was used to explore and analyze the dataset before creating the Power BI dashboard. The following SQL queries were used to calculate key performance indicators and identify customer segments with the highest marketing campaign conversion rates.

### Total Customers

```sql
SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_customers
FROM `your_project_id.Bank_marketing.MarketingData`;
```

### Overall Conversion Rate

```sql
SELECT
    COUNT(*) AS total_customers,
    SUM(CASE WHEN y = TRUE THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS subscribed_customers,
    ROUND(
        100 * SUM(CASE WHEN y = TRUE THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) / COUNT(*),
        2
    ) AS conversion_rate_percent
FROM `your_project_id.Bank_marketing.MarketingData`;
```

### Conversion Rate by Job

```sql
SELECT
    job,
    COUNT(*) AS customers,
    SUM(CASE WHEN y = TRUE THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS subscriptions,
    ROUND(
        100 * SUM(CASE WHEN y = TRUE THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) / COUNT(*),
        2
    ) AS conversion_rate_percent
FROM `your_project_id.Bank_marketing.MarketingData`
GROUP BY job
ORDER BY conversion_rate_percent DESC;
```

### Conversion Rate by Age Group

```sql
SELECT
    CASE
        WHEN age < 30 THEN 'Under 30'
        WHEN age BETWEEN 30 AND 39 THEN '30-39'
        WHEN age BETWEEN 40 AND 49 THEN '40-49'
        WHEN age BETWEEN 50 AND 59 THEN '50-59'
        ELSE '60+'
    END AS age_group,
    COUNT(*) AS customers,
    SUM(CASE WHEN y = TRUE THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS subscriptions,
    ROUND(
        100 * SUM(CASE WHEN y = TRUE THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) / COUNT(*),
        2
    ) AS conversion_rate_percent
FROM `your_project_id.Bank_marketing.MarketingData`
GROUP BY age_group
ORDER BY age_group;
```

